Phoenix Group Says Ignis Reduces Stake in Argonaut Venture

-- B y   P e t e r   W o o d i f i e l d
-- 
2011-08-23T15:57:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/phoenix-group-says-ignis-reduces-stake-in-argonaut-venture-1-.html
Phoenix Group Holdings (PGH)  Ltd., the
U.K.’s biggest manager of closed life insurance funds, said
Argonaut  Capital Partners  and Ignis Asset Management
restructured their joint venture with Argonaut taking management
control.  Argonaut will own 60 percent under the new structure with
Ignis reducing its stake by 10 percent to 40 percent, said
Phoenix in a regulatory statement today.  “Argonaut will expand its investment team and management
resource and develop its own U.K. distribution capability,”
said Phoenix. “Ignis will continue to distribute Argonaut’s
funds in Continental Europe.”  Phoenix owns Ignis Asset Management which has about 67
billion pounds ($11 billion) of assets under management.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tim Farrand at 
 tfarrand@bloomberg.net  